This abridgment has been printed by Capgrave with the addition of a section from Aelred of Rievaulx, and has been re· printed by Surius. Pinkerton’s collection contains the abridg- ment, as well as the more extended biography. Both works have been carefully collated with the MSS. by Mr. Raine for the present edition; all variatione between the original and the abridgment are pointed out; and those passages which have been rendered illegible by the fire have been supplied from Pinkerton. These are distinguished by brackets, the portions between which represent the amount of injury sustained.
